race.comment: Tough race to end the day. MASTER GEE (8) speedy gelding at his top for this from the awkward gate. Nailed late when returning to form with the 59kg when a gritty nose second over 1100m at this track. Well weighted with Boyd's claim and expected to go one better. FOUR DEGREES (3) progressive sprinter resuming with an excellent win record. Kept raising the bar last time in and wasn't asked to do much when sixth in a recent 1000m trial. Will go back from the draw and be ridden for luck. REPRISAL (6) had the three mixed runs this time in and assess on his eye catching fourth over this track and trip two-back. Saves ground along the inside and will be launching late. CHANDON STAR (5) winkers go on from the better gate and had genuine excuses when last from the outside draw over 900m at Scone. The win three-back had merit and stays in the calculations. DESERT COUGAR (9) shapes as the best of the rest after the two wins from his last three starts.
